About 116 million babies will be born during the #COVID19 pandemic. New mothers &amp; their babies face lockdowns, overwhelmed health facilities &amp; equipment shortages.

@UNICEF is calling for immediate action to protect pregnant women &amp; newborns.

https://t.co/zVBJkCqBHg

In the midst of the #COVID19 pandemic, several ongoing humanitarian crises are in need of continued life-saving support.

@UNOCHA &amp; partners call for humanitarian funding to provide assistance to the most vulnerable. https://t.co/hJrGBpckiS 

https://t.co/Xpz3ky7GzR

Lockdowns, travel restrictions &amp; other measures put in place to slow the spread of #COVID19 put human trafficking victims at risk of further exploitation.

@UNODC is working with its partners to protect the most vulnerable, including children.  

https://t.co/J56vzKFAQR

Illegal wildlife trade increases the risk of zoonotic diseases, such as #COVID19.

@UNEP explores why ending illegal wildlife trade could reduce the likelihood of future disease outbreaks. https://t.co/2eUJYIlhPh

 https://t.co/IEOsph7mv1

Nearly 19 million children were internally displaced in 2019 due to violence &amp; conflict - they are among the world's most vulnerable to #COVID19. 

@UNICEF is calling for greater efforts to protect children amid the global pandemic. 

https://t.co/v98hVcLiDf

2 million additional cases of female genital mutilation could take place by 2030 as a result of the #COVID19 pandemic.
@UNFPA is calling for steps to protect the rights &amp; dignity of all women &amp; girls. https://t.co/YEX0uH2Qyt #EndFGM

https://t.co/cCx4DEVrt3

For millions of farmers, the #COVID19 pandemic poses a significant threat to their way of life.  

@FAO is scaling up its support to farmers &amp; herders, who play an invaluable role in protecting the world's food supply.

https://t.co/7ESsW9cRYU https://t.co/gj04NW133e
